It first finds all sections with "Precondition" in them. Then, for each such section, it finds all @param tags and their corresponding content. This content is then used to populate the 'description', 'name' and 'content' fields of the precondition dictionary.

Finally, it adds a precondition for the given method name and outputs the resulting JSON object.
